  "name": {
    "en": "Stewed Chicken Legs and Heads",
    "local_name": "Miguu na Vichwa vya Kuku"
  },
  "description": "A flavorful and hearty stew that makes use of the whole chicken, featuring tender legs and gelatinous, savory heads slow-cooked in a rich, spiced tomato and onion sauce. It's a dish that maximizes flavor and nutrition from every part of the bird.",
  "origin_region": "Nationwide",
  "cultural_significance": {
    "importance": "economical_everyday_dish",
    "occasions": ["daily_meals", "family_dinners", "local_eateries", "budget_friendly_meals"],
    "cultural_notes": "This dish embodies the 'waste not, want not' philosophy common in Ugandan households. Chicken heads are a prized part for their unique, gelatinous texture and rich flavor, often enjoyed by those who appreciate offal. It's a common sight in local markets where chicken is sold in parts, and it provides an affordable way for families to enjoy a meat-based stew. The long cooking ensures the heads become tender and the legs fall-off-the-bone soft."
  },
